The number of vacant jobs in  Germany 
has risen above 1 million for the first time since 2007,
 Handelsblatt  reported today, citing numbers from the countryâ€™s
Institute for Employment Research.  The number of vacant positions stood at 1.05 million in the
first quarter of this year, an increase of 60,000 since the end
of December and 400,000 more than in the first three months of
